_data.title: Introduction

children.value: Angelists is a platform to trade placements.
Investors can buy these placements to advertise for their own or other projects.

The good site is, even if the investors is not curious about the project, she or he can use it to it it for her or his own. So he promote an configured destination, but nevertheless he will support the project where the placement is from without any risk!

_data.text:
Angelists is a platform to trade placements.

Investors can buy these placements to advertise for their own or other projects.

The good site is, even if the investors is not curious about the project, she or he can use it to it it for her or his own. So he promote an configured destination, but nevertheless he will support the project where the placement is from without any risk!

_data.text:
To configure your placement, you need to own it. Otherwise you will get the warning
If you want to own this placement, you need to buy the NFT. Or someone gives it to you as a present. # Buy NFT on Marketplace Click on the warning field as mentioned below, or buy it by clicking on the **Buy** button on the placement itself by hovering your mouse over the placement you are interested to own.
You are redirected to the Marketplace in a new Tab or Window. Here you can buy the NFT. You can buy this via fixed price, auction or make an offer. Head over to [Contribution](/configure) if you own this NFT.

_data.text:
If you own this NFT, you can now configure it. After configuration you customized placement will be shown on projects landing-pages. On the current Marketplace Opensea, you have a link to the configurator in the NFTs description.
You can configure the placement via click on **Config** button as well, which is on the projects landing-page in *Angels Section* by hovering with the mouse over the placement.
# Configuration Connect your Metamask Wallet and Sign Signature Request.
If you already own this specific placement NFT, you should see the success field **You own the NFT, this Placement is yours!** > Depending on Placement Type, you see different Input Fields available. Premium Placements have most fields.
If you own Non Premium Placement like Ruby you should see this
If you own Non Premium Placement like Silver you should see this
## Configure Premium Placement Enter any **Name** you want to show in your placement. > Fields are optional expect ***Destination Link*** and minimum one of the other fields.
Now enter a short **Discription**
You can define a **Text Color**, because if you have a light background-image, you would need a dark text color. White is default Now you can enter any **Profile Image Link**. Copy the image link form a source. Mostly you can do so by right click on the image from your source and click *Copy Image Link* > Later will be uploadable in Beta Version
If you have done that, the next field is **Banner Image Link** It works the same way as ***Profile Image Link*** above.
Now you can enter a **Destination Link**. So if people see you placement and click on it, they will be redirected to your destination.
Click on **Save** Now you are done! Congratulations, you Placement is now shown on the project landing-pages These landing-pages are defined in your NFTs Marketplace Description Alpha Version has the ***ecosis Genesis Partners*** Landing-pages - [ecosis](https://ecosis.io) - [eLabs](https://elabs.ecosis.io) - [cunoro](https://cunoro.ecosis.io) - [Angelists](https://angelists.ecosis.io) ## Configure Ruby Placement Enter any **Name** you want to show in your placement. > Fields are optional expect ***Destination Link*** and minimum one of the other fields.
Now you can enter any **Profile Image Link**. Copy the image link form a source. Mostly you can do so by right click on the image from your source and click *Copy Image Link* > Later will be uploadable in Beta Version
Now you can enter a **Destination Link**. So if people see you placement and click on it, they will be redirected to your destination.
Click on **Save** Now you are done! Congratulations, you Placement is now shown on the project landing-pages These landing-pages are defined in your NFTs Marketplace Description Alpha Version has the ***ecosis Genesis Partners*** Landing-pages - [ecosis](https://ecosis.io) - [eLabs](https://elabs.ecosis.io) - [cunoro](https://cunoro.ecosis.io) - [Angelists](https://angelists.ecosis.io) ## Configure Silver Placement Enter any **Profile Image Link**. Copy the image link form a source. Mostly you can do so by right click on the image from your source and click *Copy Image Link* > Later will be uploadable in Beta Version
Now you can enter a **Destination Link**. So if people see you placement and click on it, they will be redirected to your destination.
Click on **Save** Now you are done! Congratulations, you Placement is now shown on the project landing-pages These landing-pages are defined in your NFTs Marketplace Description Alpha Version has the ***ecosis Genesis Partners*** Landing-pages - [ecosis](https://ecosis.io) - [eLabs](https://elabs.ecosis.io) - [cunoro](https://cunoro.ecosis.io) - [Angelists](https://angelists.ecosis.io)

_data.text:
In order to use the configurator, you need to setup the network in Metamask # Polygon Network Setup Polygon Network in Metamask, if you dont already have. Switch the connected blockchain by clicking on the tab saying Main Ethereum Network, we need to add the Matic network.
Scroll down until you find Custom RPC.
Enter in the Matic Mainnet settings as follows: - Network Name: **Polygon** - New RPC URL: **https://polygon-rpc.com** or - **https://rpc-mainnet.matic.network** or - **https://rpc-mainnet.maticvigil.com** or - **https://rpc-mainnet.matic.quiknode.pro** - ChainID: **137** - Symbol: **MATIC** - Block Explorer URL: **https://polygonscan.com/**
Click **Save**. Congratulations! You now have added Polygon Network to your Metamask!

_data.text:
Now you can sell your Placement, if you like to. Head over to the marketplace and configure sell options, so other can by it from you! To do so, you either have saved your opensea NFT Link somewhere or you go the projects landing-pages, click on **Buy** and you will be redirected to you NFT on Opensea.
# Configure Sale If you own this placement, you can click on **Sell** on Opensea NFT Page
Now you should see several options. > You can click on **More Options**
Here you can configure - Price (Select Currency) - Amount - Duration After setting this up, you can **Complete Listing** You need to **Sign Transaction**. You are done!
